<TEXT>
 The Miss America Pageant is playing down the swimsuit competition this year, but a competitor hopes to draw viewers interested in more flesh. The Platinum Doll Bikini Contest, with comedian <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Byner </PERSON> as host, is one in a series of naughty contests that have sprung up over the years to counter the pageant's wholesome image. Today's contest features 36 go-go girls from <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, said contest producer <PERSON> Neil </PERSON> <PERSON> Cirucci </PERSON>. Instead of the scholarship offered by the Miss <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> program, the go-go girls will be competing for a $ 10,000 cash prize and the `` platinum G-string award,'' <PERSON> Cirucci </PERSON> said. The second-prize winner gets $ 5,000 and third prize is $ 3,000. Fourth - and fifth-place runners-up get trips to <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> The contestants were auditioned by the contest organizers _ not selected in state `` pageants'' _ and no interview was required, he said. No evening gowns in this contest _ a selection of costumes will be stripped off to reveal halters and G-strings. `` We have one girl wearing a nun outfit, another who's a cowboy, one who will be a nurse,'' he said. The winner will not be serenaded by `` There She Is'' but instead will dance down the stage to `` a good rock' n' roll band,'' <PERSON> Cirucci </PERSON> said. `` We hope to steal some thunder away from the <ORGANIZATION> Miss </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pageant </ORGANIZATION>,'' <PERSON> Cirucci </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Leonard </PERSON> <PERSON> Horn </PERSON>, director of the venerable <ORGANIZATION> Miss </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pageant </ORGANIZATION>, which crowns Miss <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> on Saturday night, called the G-string contest `` ludicrous'' and said it will not take away his audience. `` It does n't mean a thing to us,'' he said. ` It's somebody just trying to exploit us, and it will not affect us at all.'' Judges for the Platinum Doll Bikini Contest include former <ORGANIZATION> Philadelphia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Phillies </ORGANIZATION> pitcher <PERSON> Larry </PERSON> <PERSON> Christensen </PERSON>; <PERSON> Tony </PERSON> <PERSON> Bongiovi </PERSON>, uncle of rock star <PERSON> Jon </PERSON> <PERSON> Bon </PERSON> <PERSON> Jovi </PERSON> and owner of a recording studio; and <PERSON> Gennaro </PERSON> <PERSON> Meoli </PERSON>, a fashion designer for <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Sinatra </PERSON>, <PERSON> Cirucci </PERSON> said. The G-string contest is not the first time a promoter has tried to strip away some of the <ORGANIZATION> Miss </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> America </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pageant </ORGANIZATION>'s luster. In the 1970s, several Miss Nude USA pageants were held the week before Miss <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>. The G-string contest was to be held at a Boardwalk nightclub.
