<HEAD>Eagleburger Says US Doing All It Can To Admit Soviet Refugees</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Subs pvs graf 4, Many members, with two new grafs to include
Hatch quote.</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By RUTH SINAI</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A senior administration official, seeking to deflect criticism of its handling of Soviet refugees, said today the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> was doing all it can to admit as many as possible but its capabilities are limited. `` We are trying to manage the surge in Soviet emigration in the most humane and orderly way possible,'' said Deputy Secretary of State <PERSON> Lawrence </PERSON> <PERSON> Eagleburger </PERSON>. Testifying before the <ORGANIZATION> Senate </ORGANIZATION> subcommittee on immigration, <PERSON> Eagleburger </PERSON> said that while the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> applauds the recent liberalization of Soviet emigration, `` we must be honest in appraising our national ability to respond to unprecedented, unpredictable and previously unmanaged flows of people.'' Republican Sen. <PERSON> Orrin </PERSON> <PERSON> G. </PERSON> <PERSON> Hatch </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Utah </LOCATION> was sharply critical of the administration's position. `` No budget deficit, however large, should ever induce the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to abandon or compromise in any way its fundamental values'' of granting haven to `` oppressed peoples,'' he said. Many members of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> have criticized the strategy for dealing with Soviet refugees, saying the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> is limiting their entry instead of opening its arms to the unprecedented wave of emigres. `` Just when the Soviet faucets start opening, the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> government finds itself totally incapable of dealing with the results it has been pressing so many years to achieve,'' said Rep. <PERSON> Benjamin </PERSON> <PERSON> Gilman </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-N.Y. </LOCATION> `` We look like laughingstocks to the Soviets and like fools to the emigres.'' In an effort to deflect some of the criticism, Attorney General <PERSON> Dick </PERS