TION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION> but the move provides an annual opportunity to condemn the Jewish state before a large audience. Arab delegates also habitually walk out when <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s representative speaks to the <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assembly </ORGANIZATION>. <PERSON> Kelly </PERSON> denied <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> peace efforts were at a dead end. `` There is potential for movement,'' he said, adding that a timetable for face-to-face negotiations should be set by Palestinians and <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> _ not the <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> administration.
