<HEAD>With AM-Colombia</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EDMUNDSTON, New Brunswick (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Five men arrested with Venezuelan papers and an arsenal of weapons have been linked to Colombian suspects in a drug-trafficking case, authorities in this Canadian province said Friday. A <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> official said two of those arrested are known to be Colombian. The arrests Wednesday launched a flurry of speculation that the suspects came to this eastern province to interfere with a hearing Thursday for two Colombians suspected of cocaine trafficking. Canadian Mounted police confirmed that connection Friday. Asked if there was a link between the two cases, Inspector <PERSON> Al </PERSON> <PERSON> Hutchinson </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Royal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Canadian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mounted </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Police </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Fredericton </LOCATION> said, `` That's correct. `` We've re-evaluated the situation between the two groups,'' he said without elaborating. However, <PERSON> Hutchinson </PERSON> said the connection between the cases has prompted police to move the men facing drug charges from <LOCATION> Fredericton </LOCATION> city jail to a more secure prison within the province. He would not say which prison. Canadian police said they had ruled out suggestions that the suspects are hitmen sent by drug traffickers in <LOCATION> Colombia </LOCATION> to kill officials from <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION> or the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>. `` There's no threat to any <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> or Canadian government official,'' <PERSON> Hutchinson </PERSON> said in a brief statement. Canadian authorities also rejected speculation that the suspects had intended to cross the border to mount an attack at President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>'s vacation home in <LOCATION> Kennebunkport </LOCATION>, Me. In <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> late Friday, <ORGANIZATION> Secret </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Jane </PERSO