<HEAD>And Now, Vietnam _ the Musical</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MATT WOLF</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 People expect great things from <PERSON> Cameron </PERSON> <PERSON> Mackintosh </PERSON>, the producer of `` Cats,'' `` Les Miserables'' and `` The Phantom of the Opera.'' But a musical set in <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION>? That's something else. `` It's another emotional roller coaster,'' the Tony-winning millionaire said of `` Miss Saigon,'' his most-anticipated blockbuster to date. The $ 4.65 million-show, opening Sin <LOCATION> Vietnam </LOCATION> prior to the 1975 fall of <LOCATION> Saigon </LOCATION> and then picks up in 1978. The musical at the Theater Royal, Dept. 20, is set rury <PERSON> Lane </PERSON>, reworks the `` Madama Butterfly'' story about the doomed liaison between an American naval officer and his Japanese bride. It stars Welsh actor <PERSON> Jonathan </PERSON> <PERSON> Pryce </PERSON> as a Vietnamese pimp; <PERSON> Simon </PERSON> <PERSON> Bowman </PERSON> and <PERSON> Claire </PERSON> <PERSON> Moore </PERSON> as the lovesick American GI and his wife; and 18-year-old Filipino actress <PERSON> Lea </PERSON> <PERSON> Salonga </PERSON> in her Western stage debut, as <PERSON> Kim </PERSON>, the musical's tragic heroine. `` Miss Saigon'' reteams <PERSON> Mackintosh </PERSON> with <PERSON> Alain </PERSON> <PERSON> Boublil </PERSON> and <PERSON> Claude-Michel </PERSON> <PERSON> Schonberg </PERSON>, the award-winning French authors of `` <LOCATION> Les </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Miserables </LOCATION>,'' which is well on its way to being the most internationally successful musical ever. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Maltby </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, the Tony-winning Broadway director of `` Ai n't Misbehavin''' and `` Song and Dance,'' co-wrote ther over three years and its pre-opening ticket sale of $ 7.75 million is believed to be a <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> record <PERSON> Mackintosh </PERSON> said its appeal differs from that of `` <LOCATION> Les </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Miserables </LOCATION>,'' which was based on <PERSON> Victor </PERS