<TEXT>
 Here are the dates of key events in the furor over `` The Satanic Verses'': SEPT. 26, 1988 _ <ORGANIZATION> Viking </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Penguin </ORGANIZATION> publishes `` The Satanic Verses'' in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>. OCT. 5 _ <LOCATION> India </LOCATION> bans the book as offensive to <ORGANIZATION> Islam </ORGANIZATION>, the first country to do so. JAN. 14, 1989 _ Moslems publicly burn the book in <LOCATION> Bradford </LOCATION>, northern <LOCATION> England </LOCATION>. FEB. 12-13 _ Seven people are killed in anti-Rushdie rioting in <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> India </LOCATION>. FEB. 14 _ <PERSON> Ayatollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Ruhollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> calls on Moslems to kill <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON> and his publishers on grounds they insulted Islam. <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON> and his wife, <PERSON> Marianne </PERSON> <PERSON> Wiggins </PERSON>, go into hiding. FEB. 15 _ Protesters stone the <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Embassy </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Tehran </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>'s capital An Iranian cleric puts a price on <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON>'s head. FEB. 17 _ President <PERSON> Ali </PERSON> <PERSON> Khamenei </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> suggests <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON> could be pardoned if he repents. FEB. 18 _ <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON> apologizes for causing distress to Moslems. <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON> renews the death sentence, saying the statement falls short of a public repentance. FEB. 21 _ The 12-nation <ORGANIZATION> European </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Economic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Community </ORGANIZATION> withdraws its envoys from <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>. All but <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>'s return within weeks. MARCH 7 _ <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> sever diplomatic relations. MARCH 29 _ The <LOCATION> Saudi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Arabian </LOCATION> leader of Moslems in <LOCATION> Belgium </LOCATION> who criticized <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON>'s death sentence is shot dead at <LOCATION> Brussels </LOCATION>' main mosque along with an aide. AUG. 3 _ A man is killed in a bomb explosion at a <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> hotel, while purportedly preparing an attack on <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON>. AUG. 25 _ Ms. <PERSON> Wiggins </PERSON>' publishers say she has been living apart from her husband for the last month. SEPT. 1 _ In his first published literary work since `` The Satanic Verses,'' a 17-line poem in <LOCATION> Granta </LOCATION>, a British literary magazine, <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON> vows to continue writing.
