<SECOND>PM-Luxury Car Wars,0566</SECOND>
<HEAD>Lexus and Infiniti Bear Watching, Cadillac Says</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By FREDERICK STANDISH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Auto Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>AUBURN HILLS, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Cadillac should hang on to its share of the luxury car market in 1990 despite the entry of two Japanese luxury car lines this year, the division's general manager says. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Grettenberger </PERSON> also said Thursday that the popularity of <ORGANIZATION> Nissan </ORGANIZATION>'s Infiniti line and <ORGANIZATION> Toyota </ORGANIZATION>'s Lexus cars would be watched closely by Cadillac officials. Lexus cars officially went on sale Sept. 1, but some had been sold before they arrived in showrooms. Infiniti's two models go on sale Nov. 8. `` We're not taking it lightly at all,'' <PERSON> Grettenberger </PERSON> said during <ORGANIZATION> Cadillac </ORGANIZATION>'s 1990 introduction. `` I'm not surprised that Cadillac owners are susceptible.'' A survey by <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Grady </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Integrated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Automotive </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Resources </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Wayne </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Pa. </LOCATION>, showed that of 200 people who bought Lexus cars during the first month of sale, 12.2 percent of them traded in Cadillacs and 6.1 percent switched from Lincolns. Early predictions by Lexus officials forecast that about 10 percent of the cars traded in on their two models would be Cadillacs or Lincolns. Many more people would trade in European luxury cars, including Mercedes and BMW, and others would step up to Lexus from other Toyota-made cars, they said. Infiniti's two cars will be in about 50 Infiniti dealers on Nov. 8. <PERSON> Dave </PERSON> <PERSON> Hubbard </PERSON>, Infiniti's national advertising director, said Thursday the division had not predicted the kinds of cars that would be traded in. However, he added, Infiniti had a long-range goal of capturing buyers moving into the luxury segment for the first time. <PERSON> Grettenberger </PERSON> said it was understandable that a large percentage of trade-ins would be Cadillacs since <ORGANIZATION> Cadillac </ORGANIZATION> is the largest player in the luxury car market, holding about 26.8 percent of it. `` There's no question that the newest products from <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION> will represent formidable competition,'' <PERSON> Grettenberger </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Cadillac </PERSON>'s base prices for 1990 range from $ 26,960 to $ 36,980 with the Allante's prices at $ 50,900 for the new convertible-only version at $ 50,900 and $ 56,533 for the model with a removable hardtop, the same price as last year. Lexus' two cars carry base prices of $ 21,050 and $ 35,000, and Infiniti cars cost $ 23,500 and $ 38,000. `` They've done a very good job of preparing the market for the car,'' <PERSON> Grettenberger </PERSON> said of Lexus. `` It will be interesting to see if they can maintain this level over the next couple of months.'' Lexus has forecast annual sales of about 75,000 cars, about one-fourth <PERSON> Cadillac </PERSON>'s prediction. <PERSON> Hubbard </PERSON> said Infiniti would make no sales projections for the first year. <PERSON> Grettenberger </PERSON> said he expected <ORGANIZATION> Cadillac </ORGANIZATION> to continue to command the lion's share of the luxury car market. holding on to its 26.8 percent share. Asked where Lexus and Infiniti would get their buyers, <PERSON> Grettenberger </PERSON> said they most likely would come from the European makers. `` Luxury car buyers like to buy new things,'' he said. For 1990, <ORGANIZATION> Cadillac </ORGANIZATION> has kept the basic exterior designs of its entire line. It is introducing the convertible <PERSON> Allante </PERSON>, adding a traction control system for the two-seater. It also is putting more powerful engines in the <LOCATION> De </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ville </LOCATION>, Fleetwood, <LOCATION> Seville </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Eldorado </LOCATION> models. In addition, <PERSON> Cadillac </PERSON> is making other changes in all its cars, none of which will affect how the vehicles look.
