<DATELINE>BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Communications </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> today accepted a $ 1.9 billion buyout offer from <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Group </ORGANIZATION>, a sweetened bid that topped a $ 1.8 billion offer from <PERSON> Rupert </PERSON> <PERSON> Murdoch </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> increased its offer to $ 25 per share from its earlier $ 20 bid, <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Hardy </PERSON> said. Two companies controlled by <PERSON> Murdoch </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Fox </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, offered $ 23.16 a share in a surprise bid announced Tuesday <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> sealed its latest offer with a promise to promptly make a non-refundable $ 50 million deposit on <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION>, which encompasses the remainder of the old <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Artists </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> MGM </ORGANIZATION> movie studios. Under the terms of the agreement, <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> would acquire all of <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION>'s outstanding common stock for $ 25 per share and all its preferred stock for $ 18 per share, she said. <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> negotiated with <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Fox </PERSON> until late Thursday, but then ended their talks. <PERSON> Howard </PERSON> <PERSON> Rubenstein </PERSON>, a <PERSON> Murdoch </PERSON> spokesman, said <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> had approached him about a buyout. `` He thought he had a deal, but then the transaction fell apart,'' <PERSON> Rubenstein </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> has spent 18-months trying to find a buyer satisfactory to <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION>'s controlling shareholder <PERSON> Kirk </PERSON> <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON>, who has repeatedly sold and then repurchased many of the assets of the studios. The <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> deal provides for $ 1.33 billion to be paid for <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION>'s common stock, $ 180 million for its preferred stocks, and $ 400 million in junk bond debt that <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> is assuming. <PERSON> Murdoch </PERSON>'s offer valued <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> at about $ 1.8 billion, including the debt. A previous <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> deal would essentially split <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION>, with <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> paying about $ 600 million for the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Artists </ORGANIZATION> studio and some other assets. It would have given the famous lion logo, the <ORGANIZATION> MGM </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> TV </ORGANIZATION> operations, a library of 34 recent movies, and the <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> headquarters building in <LOCATION> Beverly </LOCATION> hills to <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON>. But under the agreement announced today, there would be no repurchase of any <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION>'s assets or any investments in <ORGANIZATION> Qintex </ORGANIZATION> by former <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> shareholders. <PERSON> Kerkorian </PERSON> owns 82 percent of <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION>'s common stock and all but a tiny fraction of the preferred stock. However, <ORGANIZATION> MGM </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Grand </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a Kerkorian-controlled company that operates a first-class airline and <LOCATION> Nevada </LOCATION> casinos, will purchase the <ORGANIZATION> MGM-UA </ORGANIZATION> headquarters building in October for $ 43 million or its