wer to 3 cents higher with September at $ 3.88 -RCB- a bushel; corn was 2 \ cents lower to 1 \ cents higher with September at $ 2.35 a bushel; oats were -LCB- cent lower to 2 -LCB- cents higher with September at $ 1.37 a bushel; soybeans were 2 cents lower to 1 cent higher with September at $ 5.83 -LCB- a Livestock and meat futures were mixed on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> in a day of profit-taking following Thursday's fierce rally, which was prompted by proposals to include pork products in a food-aid package to <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION>. Live cattle futures settled .07 cent lower to .45 cent higher with October at 72.45 cents a pound; feeder cattle were .15 cent lower to .05 cent higher with September at 83.37 cents a pound; hogs were .32 cent to .55 cent higher with October at 40.97 cents a pound; frozen pork bellies were .15 cent lower to .05 cent higher with February at 48.25 cents a pound.
