<HEAD>Meat on the Hoof Offered By International Satellite Link</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JOHN K. WILEY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SPOKANE, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Buyers in <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Zealand </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION> can bid on <ORGANIZATION> Hereford </ORGANIZATION> cattle being sold here Sunday in what is believed to be the first international satellite auction of registered beef cattle, organizers said Friday. The first international satellite sale of registered beef cattle will be beamed throughout the world and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> to television viewers who call in their bids to a telephone bank at the auction here. `` We feel like this is going to be the way to go in the future,'' said <PERSON> Willard </PERSON> <PERSON> Wolf </PERSON>, the <ORGANIZATION> Northwest </ORGANIZATION> representative of the American <ORGANIZATION> Hereford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> who proposed the satellite auction after attending a similar `` sky bridge'' between <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> and Australian wheat farmers last January. Cattle ranchers in <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Zealand </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Canada </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> can buy from 26 consignments of registered <ORGANIZATION> Hereford </ORGANIZATION> bulls, heifers, semen and embryos by telephone and save the costs of traveling to the auction, <PERSON> Wolf </PERSON> said. `` The price of an airline ticket would buy enough semen to inseminate 20 cows,'' said <PERSON> Wolf </PERSON>, a <LOCATION> Spokane </LOCATION> rancher and co-chairman of the event. `` This way, a breeder in <LOCATION> Australia </LOCATION> can make a $ 25 telephone call and save the cost of a ticket.'' `` You no longer have to be in the heat of cattle country to have a significant cattle sale,'' said <PERSON> Carey </PERSON> <PERSON> Hegreberg </PERSON>, program coordinator and <ORG